SIMPLE: primer
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Primer
<hw>Prim"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, primes</def>; specifically, <def>an instrument or device for
priming; esp., a cap, tube, or water containing percussion powder or
other compound for igniting a charge of gunpowder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Primer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Primer
<hw>Prim"er</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>primer</ets>,
<ets>primier</ets>, <ets>premier</ets>, F. <ets>premier</ets>. See
<er>Premier</er>.]</ety> <def>First; original; primary.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>primer</xex> English kings.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Primer fine</b></col> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld>, <cd>a
fine due to the king on the writ or commencement of a suit by fine.</cd>
<au>Blackstone.</au> -- <col><b>Primer seizin</b></col> <fld>(Feudal
Law)</fld>, <cd>the right of the king, when a tenant <xex>in
capite</xex> died seized of a knight's fee, to receive of the heir, if
of full age, one year's profits of the land if in possession, and half a
year's profits if the land was in reversion expectant on an estate for
life; -- now abolished.</cd> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Primer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Primer
<hw>Prim"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Originally, the book
read at <ets>prime</ets>, the first canonical hour. LL. <ets>primae
liber</ets>. See <er>Prime</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 4.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Originally, a small prayer book for church service, containing the
little office of the Virgin Mary; also, a work of elementary religious
instruction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>primer</qex>, or office of the Blessed Virgin.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small elementary book for teaching children to
read; a reading or spelling book for a beginner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As he sat in the school at his <qex>prymer</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>A kind of type, of which there
are two species; one, called <stype>long primer</stype>, intermediate in
size between bourgeois and small pica [see <er>Long primer</er>]; the
other, called <stype>great primer</stype>, larger than pica.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note><centered><point18><greatprimertype>Great primer
type.</greatprimertype></point18></centered></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Primero</ent>⟦br⟧
